<h1>@Vte{{}} @HI{{kudasai}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <strong>@Vte{{}} @HI{{kudasai}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@Vte{{}} @HI{{kudasai}}</strong> is an expression used to ask, instruct or encourage
the listener to do something. It cannot be used to a superior.
</p>

<p>
When used to ask the listener to do something, it is often preceded by @HI{{sumimasenga}}.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{sumimasenga, kono@KJ{{sino-^character}}no@KJ{{read}}mi@KJ{{direction}}wo
      @KJ{{teach}}ete kudasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Excuse me, could you tell me how to read this kanji please?
  </td> </tr>
</table>      
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kokoni @KJ{{dwell^place}}to @KJ{{name^in*front}}wo @KJ{{write}}ite kudasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Please write your name and address here.
  </td> </tr>
</table>      
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

